==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Desponsation
<hw>Des`pon*sa"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>desponsatio</ets>: cf. OF. <ets>desponsation</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
betrothing; betrothal.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For all this <qex>desponsation</qex> of her . . . she had not set
one step toward the consummation of her marriage.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Desponsory</ent>⟦br⟧
